comments.body:
Pieter suggested to add a metadata field to authorization server metadata that indicates if sender constraint tokens are supported or not. 

@PieterKas would that field be general about "cnf" is supported or should it rather be "assertion with requested_cnf is supported"?

Update (discussed during the call): It should be the latter. Maybe 
```
{
   "requested_cnf_supported": true
}
```
?
